    "# Vectors\n",
    "In this notebook, you will get practice working with and plotting 2d vectors! Vectors are ordered lists of numbers with both direction and magnitude. When we have a lot of information or data (neural spikes, fMRI, EEG, behavioral data, etc), we can represent them using vectors. The field of linear algebra gives us a way to work with these vectors and perform operations on them. \n",
    "\n",
    "Vectors generally have the following notation: $$\\vec{x} = \\begin{bmatrix} x_1 \\\\ x_2 \\\\ x_3 \\\\ \\vdots \\\\ x_n\\end{bmatrix}$$"
   ]
  },
